{"id":1245416728,"question_id":525,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1714449060,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"24 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1245416728/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Contiguous Array","memory":"55.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int findMaxLength(int[] nums) {\n\n        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        map.put(0, -1);\n\n        int cur = 0;\n        int max= 0 ;\n\n        int len = nums.length;\n        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n            int n = nums[i];\n\n            cur += (n==1)? 1 : -1;\n\n            if(map.containsKey(cur)){\n                max = Math.max(max, i-map.get(cur));\n            }else{\n                map.put(cur, i);\n            }\n        }\n        \n\n        return max;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"contiguous-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
